[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Hey guys. What you are looking at right now is an offline app that can generate any type of image. And yes, I mean literally any type of image you can imagine. And it works on both Android and iOS, whether it\'s an iPad or an iPhone.'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This app can chat completely without the internet. And no matter what you ask, it will never refuse your request. On top of that, it can also understand images and PDFs. You upload a photo and it tells you exactly what\'s inside it.'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'You give it a document or PDF and it can answer questions about the entire file like your own personal AI assistant. And if offline AI is not enough for you, you can also connect it to cloud AI providers like Deep Seek, Gemini,'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'OpenAI, and more. So basically, you get both worlds in one app. But wait, it gets even crazier. This app can also work as a local AI server. That means you can use your'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'offline AI models as an API over your Wi-Fi network from any device. And if you know a little bit about AI models, this app supports both Light RT and GGUF models.'

[01:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Light RT gives you higher speed and smoother performance. And with GGUF support, you can download and try any model from Hugging Face directly. So Nora and I built this app together and we decided to make it completely'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'open source and fully free to use. No ads, no subscriptions, and no hidden paywalls. This app literally took us weeks of work, testing, fixing bugs, and optimizing every little thing.'

[01:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So if you appreciate the effort, a quick subscribe would really mean a lot. But before you install this app on your phone, there are a few things you should understand. When you open the app for the first time, you need to download a'

[01:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
